title: For Sale:  Thompson Contender With (4) Barrels LOOK!!
postcontent: The original Contender, now known as the generation one (G1) Contender, was replaced by the G2 Contender soon after the Encore came out. The G2 Contender is essentially dimensionally the same as the original Contender, but uses an Encore style trigger group. Due to the changes in the trigger mechanism, and to differences in the angle of the grip relative to the boreline of the gun, the buttstocks and pistol grips are different between the G1 and G2 Contenders and will not interchange. The G2, though, uses essentially the same barrels and fore-ends as the original Contender[6] and barrels will interchange, with the only two exceptions being the G2 muzzleloading barrels, which will only fit the G2 frame, and the Herrett barrels/fore-ends, which are specific for use only on a G1 frame.[7] Unlike the original Contender, dry-firing of the G2 Contender is possible only in the center (safe) hammer position, located on the hammer between the centerfire and rimfire positions. Also, unlike the original Contender, the break-action does not need to be opened/closed (cycled) to practice dry-firing, provided the hammer is lowered between dry firing "shots". The adjustability of G2 Contender triggers is also slightly different from the original G1 Contender. This is serial number 218507 and comes with a stainless 12" ported 45-70 gov't barrel, 14", 30-30 WIN Super 14 barrel, 10", 44 MAG barrel and a 14" 45 Colt / 410 Barrel. This is a fantastic gun in around 95% original condition so look close at this gun for your hunting and collecting needs.

title: For Sale:  Glock 26, gen 3, nickel boron finish!! Perfect carry 9mm! Like New!!
postcontent:
Up for sale is my generation 3 Glock 26. This pistol has the nickel Boron coating over Glocks standard tennifer on the slide, internals, and barrel. In case you are unfamiliar with nickel Boron, it is an ion bonding process that results in a finish that is like stainless steel in appearance, however, it has a lifetime warranty to NEVER chip, crack, or rust. This stuff is near indestructible. I have seen torture test that are unbelievable. People have left guns with this coating in Salt water for 12 months without a single spot of corrosion. They also say you don't have to ever clean or lubricate the gun because the nickel boron has high lubricity. All you ever do is give it a quick wipe and pass a patch down the barrel. However, having said that, this gun has been cleaned regularly anyway.

This pistol is in like new condition. I bought it new and have put maybe 75 rounds through it. I'm only selling to make room for a new purchase. The pistol comes in the original box, with two magazines. One of the magazines has a finger grip extender that makes drawing and firing much easier. The grip has a rubberized talon decal to help with the grip, but if you don't like it you can remove it. Also comes with the factory speed loader and a nice leather in the waistband holster from Tagua. Let me know if you have any questions, and thanks for looking!

This little gem is a rare and complete 25 auto. It's not pristine on the outside but still a good shooter. The grips alone sell for over $300. Fits in your pants pocket, purse or?? Light weight and 6-round magazine. Known as the Model ‘N’ internally within Colt, the 1908 Vest Pocket is a diminutive 4.5 inches long, and sports a 2 inch barrel. Weighing a mere 13 ounces, it is fed by a six round single column magazine. The pistol’s fixed open iron sights were rather small and rudimentary, but typical for small hideout automatics of its era and adequate for the short range at which it was intended to be used. The Model 1908, has a standard slide-locking safety catch, as well as a grip safety.

title: For Sale:  8mm Yugo Mauser M24/47
location: Youngsville, Raleigh / Durham / CH, North Carolina
postcontent:
Selling only, no trades. Quality M24/47 Yugoslavian Mauser in 8mm. Only have shot 50 or so rounds through it. Mirror bore (probably new barrel) and very smooth action. Straight bolt. Just google the M24/47 to get an idea of the quality rifle this surplus is - for a low price. Imported by Samco. Non-matching serial numbers but functions very well. Head space checked by importer and fired by me without issue. Finish is at least 75% and stock is good, no cracks. Cosmoline free! Has front sight hood and cleaning rod. No bayonet. There is one small wood fix in upper hand guard. But it is very very accurate, and very pretty. Would make a great deer hunting rifle with a scout scope. I also have 150 or so Yugo surplus 198 grain FMJ 8mm rounds left (from the 50's) that go bang every time. Better ammo is recommended but I'll sell the rounds off for a bargain if interested ($0.40 per). Rifle comes with a new leather repro sling from the era. 

I love it but it kicks me like a mule and I don't have the resources to properly scope it. The iron sights on Mausers are a bit tough to see lol. 

Great project rifle or just shoot as-is. Lots of fun!
